You enter the room and almost slip and fall. The floor seems to be covered in intermittent patches of ice, with (again) a door to the North.
You idly wonder what hyper-imaginative entity constructed this fantastical place.
There is shelf to your left with a steel ball sitting atop it. To your right, there is an intricate series of pipes.
#ROOM_STATE_1#
This room has an icy floor, a series of tubes, a door to the North and a shelf to your left with a ball on it.
#ROOM_STATE_2#
The ball traveled in a Rube-Goldberd-fashion through the pipes. The door to the North was unlocked and remains that way.